The defendant Alexis T Moser was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500), a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant. State advised the Court they have complied with the Victims' Rights Law.   

Defendant sentenced to serve 90 days in the House of Correction, concurrent to Waukesha County Case No. 15CF1332 but consecutive to any other sentence, with credit for 7 days time served.  COURT STAYED THE SENTENCE and placed the defendant on probation with the State of Wisconsin, Department of Corrections for a period of 12 MONTHS. Court allows probation to be transfered to Waukesha County. May terminate probation after 6 months if deemed appropriate by agent. If revoked, Court allows HUBER for child care only.

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:
     *   Defendant to participate in Alcohol and Drug Assessment
          and successfully complete recommended treatment
          including random urine screens.
     *   Maintain absolute sobriety.  Defendant NOT possess or
          use any controlled substances unless by valid prescription.
     *   Successfully complete any other counseling and/or
          treatment deemed appropriate.
     *   No contact with any Walmart or Angela S.
     *   Pay all mandatory costs and surcharges by the end
          of probation. Failure to pay will result in a civil judgment.
     *   Obtain and maintain (full-time) employment, school, or
          combination of both.
     *   Restitution is set at $0.00.
     *   No illegal drugs.

Upon successful completion of the sentence Court will allow for expungement.
